This paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The specific problem being studied involves the allocation of multiple identical items between a buyer and a seller, which falls under the category of bilateral trade (cs.DS). The paper also considers the properties of dominant strategy incentive compatibility, budget balance, and individual rationality, which are key concepts in mechanism design and economic theory (cs.EC). The use of valuation functions suggests a connection to artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI), while the approximation results involve optimization and algorithms (cs.LG).
